    "sections": {
        "description": "<p><a href=\"https://milandinic.com/wordpress/plugins/disable-automatic-background-updates/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Plugin homepage</a> | <a href=\"https://milandinic.com/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Plugin author</a> | <a href=\"https://milandinic.com/donate/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Donate</a></p>\n<p>This plugin disables every type of background automatic update (for core, plugins, themes, and languages) automatically, without need to manually choose any setting or option.</p>\n<p>It is a very lightweight, it has no settings, just activate it and it works immediately.</p>\n<p>And it&#8217;s on <a href=\"https://github.com/dimadin/disable-automatic-background-updates\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">GitHub</a>.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload <code>disable-automatic-background-updates</code> folder to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress</li>\n</ol>\n"
